race.comment: SPIETHTACULAR (6) resumes here but the form she showed in her first preparation was more than good enough to be competitive in a race of this nature. Has a win and a second from two spins around this circuit and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Ticks plenty of boxes for a race like this. KING KRYPTOS (4) is a four-time winner here who draws low and gets 3kg off with the claim. Top-three aspirations if he brings his A-game. CHERBOURG (1) saves his best form for this circuit and should be hitting the line with gusto first-up. SPIRIT OF BRODIE (2) strips fitter second-up from the break and shouldn't be underestimated.
